President Obama has signed an emergency declaration for the State of Connecticut due to the conditions caused by Hurricane Irene. This declaration allows federal aid to supplement state and local response efforts. The Department of Homeland Security, Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA), will coordinate all disaster relief efforts to alleviate the hardship and suffering caused by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to provide necessary equipment and resources, and emergency protective measures will be funded at 75 percent federal funding. Gary Stanley has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.